// // This module generates a reset signal based on the status of a locked signal. When the locked input is HIGH (indicating an unlocked condition), the reset output will be HIGH, effectively signaling a reset condition. Conversely, when the locked input is LOW, the reset output will be LOW, indicating that no reset is required.
module top_module(locked,reset);input locked; 
 output reset; 
 assign reset = ~locked; 
 endmodule
